2026-04-21 02:41:02 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Power Flow Indicator (green) 5', 'Power Flow Indicator Resistor 5'] hypothesis_explanation='The Power Flow Indicator (green) LED and its resistor in Control Module 5 are missing. While these are normally in parallel to the main current path and should not affect circuit continuity, if the circuit was designed such that their absence creates an open circuit (either due to PCB layout or wiring that relies on their physical presence), then no current would flow past Control Module 5. This would result in no switch indicators lighting up and no output at the load module, matching the system symptoms observed. The battery supply LED in the power module is still on because it is independently wired. The visual inspections up to Control Module 4 found no issues, and Control Module 5 is the first module in the chain missing its indicator and associated resistor.'
